            <h3>1. What is the basic economic problem?</h3>
            <div class="options">
                <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="A"> A. Inflation</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="B"> B. Unemployment</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="C"> C. Scarcity</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="D"> D. Poverty</label>
            </div>
        </div>
    
        <div class="question">
            <h3>2. In a market economy, who determines the prices of goods and services?</h3>
            <div class="options">
                <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="A"> A. The government</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="B"> B. Central banks</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="C"> C. Supply and demand</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="D"> D. International organizations</label>
            </div>
        </div>
    
        <div class="question">
            <h3>3. What is the law of demand?</h3>
            <div class="options">
                <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="A"> A. As the price of a good increases, demand decreases</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="B"> B. As the price of a good decreases, demand decreases</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="C"> C. As the price of a good increases, demand increases</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="D"> D. Demand is unaffected by price changes</label>
            </div>
        </div>
    
        <div class="question">
            <h3>4. What does GDP stand for in economics?</h3>
            <div class="options">
                <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="A"> A. Gross Domestic Product</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="B"> B. Government Development Plan</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="C"> C. Global Development Program</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q4" value="D"> D. Gross Demand Projection</label>
            </div>
        </div>
    
        <div class="question">
            <h3>5. What is meant by "opportunity cost"?</h3>
            <div class="options">
                <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="A"> A. The amount of money needed to buy a good</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="B"> B. The cost of an alternative that is foregone when a decision is made</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="C"> C. The total expenses of a business</label>
                <label><input type="radio" name="q5" value="D"> D. The price of goods and services in the market</label>
            </div>
        </div>
    
        <button type="button" id="submit-btn" onclick="submitQuiz()" style="padding: 10px 20px; border-radius:10px; font-family:gilroy; background:#40A2E3; color:white;">Submit Quiz</button>
    </form>
    

